{
  "title": "Austin's Public Pools",
  "subtitle": "A City Anatomy Story",
  "loop": true,
  "autoplay": true,
  "initialCamera": {
    "center": [-97.7431, 30.2672],
    "zoom": 10,
    "pitch": 0,
    "bearing": 0
  },

  "layers": [
    {
      "id": "pool-areas",
      "type": "fill",
      "source": "data/pool-areas.geojson",
      "paint": {
        "fill-color": "#0067c5",
        "fill-opacity": 0
      },
      "transitionOpacity": 0.35,
      "transitionDuration": 700,
      "insertBefore": "road-label"
    },
    {
      "id": "parks",
      "type": "fill",
      "source": "data/parks.geojson",
      "paint": {
        "fill-color": "#2b8a3e",
        "fill-opacity": 0
      },
      "transitionOpacity": 0.2,
      "transitionDuration": 700,
      "insertBefore": "road-label"
    },
    {
      "id": "creek-corridors",
      "type": "line",
      "source": "data/creek-corridors.geojson",
      "paint": {
        "line-color": "#1d8ca0",
        "line-opacity": 0,
        "line-width": 3
      },
      "transitionOpacity": 0.9,
      "transitionDuration": 800
    }
  ],

  "scenes": [
    {
      "id": "overview",
      "transition": "fly",
      "duration": 7000,
      "camera": {
        "center": [-97.7431, 30.2672],
        "zoom": 10.5,
        "pitch": 35,
        "bearing": -10,
        "speed": 0.5,
        "curve": 1.2
      },
      "showLayers": ["parks"],
      "hideLayers": ["pool-areas", "creek-corridors"],
      "popup": {
        "lngLat": [-97.7431, 30.2672],
        "anchor": "bottom",
        "title": "Austin's Public Pool Network",
        "subtitle": "22 facilities across the city",
        "body": "<p>Austin operates one of the most diverse public swimming programs in Texas — from century-old spring-fed pools to modern splash pads in every council district.</p>",
        "stats": [
          { "label": "Total Facilities", "value": "22" },
          { "label": "Splash Pads", "value": "9" },
          { "label": "Lap Pools", "value": "4" }
        ],
        "link": {
          "href": "/apps/citywide/PoolOpenings/",
          "text": "View Pool Status Map →"
        }
      }
    },

    {
      "id": "barton-springs",
      "transition": "fly",
      "duration": 6000,
      "camera": {
        "center": [-97.7698, 30.2629],
        "zoom": 16.5,
        "pitch": 55,
        "bearing": 90,
        "speed": 0.75,
        "curve": 1.4
      },
      "showLayers": ["pool-areas", "creek-corridors"],
      "hideLayers": ["parks"],
      "popup": {
        "lngLat": [-97.7698, 30.2629],
        "title": "Barton Springs Pool",
        "subtitle": "900 Barton Springs Rd · Zilker Park",
        "body": "<p>Fed by underground springs at a constant 68°F, Barton Springs has been Austin's outdoor living room since 1917. The 3-acre pool draws over 800,000 visitors annually.</p>",
        "stats": [
          { "label": "Water Temp", "value": "68°F year-round" },
          { "label": "Pool Size", "value": "~3 acres" },
          { "label": "Open Since", "value": "1917" }
        ],
        "link": {
          "href": "/apps/citywide/PoolOpenings/",
          "text": "Check Current Status →"
        }
      }
    },

    {
      "id": "barton-drone-reveal",
      "transition": "ease",
      "duration": 5500,
      "camera": {
        "zoom": 17.5,
        "pitch": 72,
        "bearing": 200,
        "duration": 3000
      },
      "showLayers": ["pool-areas"],
      "hideLayers": [],
      "popup": {
        "lngLat": [-97.7698, 30.2629],
        "title": "Barton Springs from Above",
        "subtitle": "In the heart of Zilker Park",
        "youtube": {
          "videoId": "F-3bPOhHEDk",
          "startAt": 4,
          "stopAt": 28,
          "mute": true
        },
        "body": "<p>The natural spring outflow carved these curves — the pool boundary follows Barton Creek's original floodplain geometry.</p>"
      }
    },

    {
      "id": "deep-eddy",
      "transition": "fly",
      "duration": 6500,
      "camera": {
        "center": [-97.7707, 30.2819],
        "zoom": 16,
        "pitch": 50,
        "bearing": -45,
        "speed": 0.7
      },
      "showLayers": ["pool-areas"],
      "hideLayers": ["creek-corridors"],
      "popup": {
        "lngLat": [-97.7707, 30.2819],
        "title": "Deep Eddy Pool",
        "subtitle": "401 Deep Eddy Ave · West Austin",
        "body": "<p>Built in 1915, Deep Eddy holds the title of Texas's oldest public pool. Its lakeside location made it a natural gathering spot during the early 20th century.</p>",
        "stats": [
          { "label": "Established", "value": "1915" },
          { "label": "Lane Length", "value": "25 yards" },
          { "label": "Admission", "value": "$3 adults" }
        ]
      }
    },

    {
      "id": "citywide-access",
      "transition": "fly",
      "duration": 7500,
      "camera": {
        "center": [-97.7431, 30.3050],
        "zoom": 11,
        "pitch": 45,
        "bearing": 15,
        "speed": 0.55,
        "curve": 1.2
      },
      "showLayers": ["parks", "pool-areas"],
      "hideLayers": ["creek-corridors"],
      "popup": {
        "lngLat": [-97.7431, 30.3050],
        "title": "Citywide Pool Access",
        "subtitle": "Distribution by council district",
        "body": "<p>Districts 1, 2, and 3 — covering East and Southeast Austin — have fewer facilities per capita than the west side. The city's Aquatics Plan proposes two new splash pads in District 1 by 2027.</p>",
        "stats": [
          { "label": "District 1", "value": "2 pools" },
          { "label": "District 6", "value": "5 pools" },
          { "label": "Drive time gap", "value": "~12 min" }
        ],
        "link": {
          "href": "/apps/citywide/PoolOpenings/",
          "text": "Explore the Interactive Map →"
        }
      }
    },

    {
      "id": "barton-creek-watershed",
      "transition": "fly",
      "duration": 7000,
      "camera": {
        "center": [-97.8100, 30.2450],
        "zoom": 12,
        "pitch": 40,
        "bearing": -20,
        "speed": 0.6
      },
      "showLayers": ["creek-corridors", "parks"],
      "hideLayers": ["pool-areas"],
      "popup": {
        "lngLat": [-97.8100, 30.2450],
        "title": "Barton Creek Watershed",
        "subtitle": "The source of Austin's spring water",
        "body": "<p>Barton Springs owes its clarity to the Edwards Aquifer recharge zone — 97 sq mi of Hill Country limestone that filters rainfall before it resurfaces at the Barton Springs fault.</p>",
        "stats": [
          { "label": "Watershed Area", "value": "97 sq mi" },
          { "label": "Spring Flow", "value": "40–60 cfs" },
          { "label": "Water Temp", "value": "68°F constant" }
        ],
        "link": {
          "href": "https://www.bseacd.org",
          "text": "Barton Springs Edwards Aquifer District →",
          "external": true
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
